  "headline": "Emotional Intelligence",
  "description": "Emotional Intelligence (EQ, Goleman 1995) is the ability to recognize, understand, and manage emotions — in yourself and others. Components: self-awareness, self-regulation, motivation, empathy, social skills. EQ is a better predictor of career success than IQ (Goleman claims — debated but widely accepted).",
